Description: Painted sycomore fig wood shabti of Aset, priestess of Amun, with a black lappet wig, a carved yellow face with black features, a red and yellow collar, unmarked hands, the body is white, the legs are inscribed with a central column of black painted Hieroglyphs on a yellow ground with two black borders.
Condition: fair - split at the back, paint worn
Acquisition name: Purchased from: Somerset Lowry-Corry, 2nd Earl of Belmore
